Giants 10, Pirates 2
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Kirk Rueter beat the Pittsburgh Pirates as much with his
bat as with his arm, driving in four runs with three hits to back his two-run
pitching as the San Francisco Giants cruised to a 10-2 victory Thursday. Bill
Mueller and Jeff Kent homered as the Giants won three of four in the series to
increase their NL West lead over idle Arizona to three games.
</P>
