<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 42; Nasdaq Rises 46  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks opened higher Friday, extending broad
gains from Thursday on optimism that the U.S. economy is growing at
a healthy rate.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 41.81 at 11,256.91.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index was up 46.38 at 4,252.78. The
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 6.76 at 1,524.44.
</P>
<P>
   Unemployment figures released Friday sent mixed signals, but
investors interpreted the numbers to mean that inflationary
pressures are under control.
</P>
<P>
   The unemployment rate edged up to 4.1 percent in August and
total payrolls fell by a bigger-than-expected 105,000 during the
month, the largest drop in nine years.
</P>
<P>
   But most of the decline in total employment, which is seasonally
adjusted, came from the departure of 158,000 temporary Census
workers and the impact of striking workers at Verizon, the nation's
largest local phone company and wireless business, the Labor
Department said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, investors are hungry again for technology stocks,
which has boosted the broader markets during recent sessions.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was up 2.06 at 539.95.
</P>
