   The American Foundation for AIDS Research wasn't saying who made
the bid for the one-of-a-kind case during a celebrity auction held
Thursday at a benefit gala here. Hollywood stars are in town for
Venice's annual film festival.
</P>
<P>
   Stone's creation has nine little drawers for lipsticks and blush
and a glass pullout tray for mixing colors.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Gere's lion made of golden Murano glass -- so heavy two
people had to hold it up during the auction -- went for $11,000.
</P>
<P>
   Stone herself made the biggest bid of the night, offering
$150,000 for a portrait to be done by Julian Schnabel, who won fame
by smashing plates and making portraits out of the fragments. For
now, no one is saying who the subject will be.
</P>
